headlines.description: — Ja Morant scored six of his 26 points in the final 30 seconds, including the go-ahead basket, allowing the Memphis Grizzlies to extend their winning streak to six with a 110-106 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant scores 26, Grizzlies beat Cavs for 6th straight win

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet scored 33 points, Pascal Siakam had 18 points and 12 rebounds, and the Toronto Raptors extended their winning streak to three by beating the San Antonio Spurs 129-104 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: VanVleet tops 30 for third straight game, Raptors rout Spurs

events.name: Indiana Pacers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — RJ Barrett scored 24 of his 32 points in the first half, Julius Randle had 30 points and 16 rebounds in his first game after coming off the COVID-19 health and safety protocols list, and the New York Knicks beat the Indiana Pacers 104-94 on Tuesday...
headlines.shortLinkText: Barrett has 32, Randle has big return as Knicks beat Pacers

events.name: Phoenix Suns at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 33 points, Chris Paul added 11 points and 15 assists, and the Phoenix Suns beat the New Orleans Pelicans 123-110 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 33, leads Suns to 123-110 win over Pelicans

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James scored 14 of his 31 points in the fourth quarter, Malik Monk added 11 of his 24 in the final seven minutes, and the Los Angeles Lakers held off the Sacramento Kings 122-114 on Tuesday night for their fourth win in five games.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron, Monk lead Lakers' late rally past Kings, 122-114
